---
const painPoints = [
  "You've tried to just 'push through' but nothing changes",
  "You feel like you're constantly masking or performing for everyone around you",
  "Small tasks feel impossibly overwhelming and you can't explain why",
  "You know something isn't right but you're not sure where to start",
];
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)]">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="mb-4">Sound familiar?</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-light)] text-lg mb-10">I hear these from clients all the time. You're not alone in feeling this way.</p>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      {painPoints.map((point) => (
        <div class="border-l-4 border-[var(--color-gold)] pl-6 py-3">
          <p class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed text-lg">{point}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-light)] mt-10 text-lg">
      If any of that resonates — you're not broken. You might just need the right support.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
